[SN]TITLE[SN]
Missing Llanarth Court psychiatric patient 'risk'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A psychiatric patient who has absconded from an Abergavenny hospital could pose a "potential risk", police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Keiron Miller, 28, went missing from Llanarth Court Psychiatric Hospital at about 09:50 BST on Friday.
Gwent Police said he was an involuntary patient at the hospital, and described him as about 5ft 10in (1.78m) tall and slim with short brown hair.
Police said there may be a "potential risk to the public" and warned people not to approach him but to call 101.
Mr Miller has links in the Barry area.
